cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.SE 

The paper deals with randomness testing, which is a topic that falls under information theory. Therefore, cs.IT is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the testing of pseudorandom number generators, which is a topic that falls under computer security (cs.CR). The use of data compression methods and statistical tests suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.CC (computational complexity). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed tests in software engineering, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.SE (software engineering).
